## GSoC Project

### Title

Merge Probabilistic Global And LAM Branches Into The Current `neural-lam` Package Hierarchy

### Abstract

This project will merge the `prob_model_global` and `prob_model_lam` branches into the current `neural-lam` repository without changing the repository structure. The project will add the missing probabilistic model family under `neural_lam/models/`, integrate global forecasting as a datastore inside `neural_lam/datastore/`, and extend the existing `train_model.py`, `ARForecaster`, and `ForecasterModule` flow so deterministic, probabilistic, LAM, and global workflows all live in one package-first hierarchy.

### Problem Statement

At present the project is split across three strengths:

- the current repo has the best final hierarchy and testing scaffold
- `prob_model_lam` contains the probabilistic LAM implementation
- `prob_model_global` contains the probabilistic global implementation

The missing work is to land the two probabilistic branches **inside** the current hierarchy.

### Main Goal

Merge the earlier branches into the current repo so that this repository becomes the final home for:

- deterministic LAM models
- probabilistic LAM models
- global probabilistic forecasting
- shared graph and training infrastructure

### Non-Goals

- no repository-wide restructuring
- no return to the old top-level branch layout
- no duplicate training stack beside the current `StepPredictor` -> `ARForecaster` -> `ForecasterModule` pipeline

